How can we not feel our planet crying out for us to protect it?  To recognize that we are hurting it?  Even if you live in the city, you still have to realize that you need the animals, insects, and vegetation on this planet in order to survive.  We need to love and nurture this planet as if it was our child.  I mean, how can your heart not skip a beat when you are amongst nature?  How can you not feel the need to appreciate it? Tension building....._Ì«_åà_Ì«Ì¨ÌàRed Velvet Mites (family Trombidiidae) are so small that they can walk on water without breaking the surface tension. This adult was only about 2mm long, and you can certainly see where these creatures get their name from! Fear not their appearance nor their bite - these arachnids only ever feed on invertebrates! As larvae they are parasitic, but as adults they take on a predatory lifestyle, hunting for tiny creatures mainly found living in the soil. They provide great benefits to controlling certain pest populations in the wild, with aphids and parasitic mites forming a part of their diet. While mites are often thought of negatively by the general public, they are not all so bad! Despite being such a diverse group of organisms, mites are usually so minute that most are poorly understood.

Ninety percent of an iceberg is usually under water, and this frozen freshwater typically melts faster below the surface of the sea than above. Sometimes during this process, as the melting freshwater rises in the ocean it breaks into plumes, like rising thunderheads, mixing in more warm water. That melts channels in the sides of icebergs, creating seams, like ribs, in the underwater portion of the iceberg, says Richard Alley, a Penn State geologist and ice expert. When sunshine and warm air melt ice above the surface, the iceberg slowly rises, exposing these achingly beautiful vertical flutes, which we saw during our journey along the western Antarctic Peninsula. This Mayan totem was in alignment with my Mayan birth chart, acquired a few days before. It's a totem of life force, fire, vitality, raw and vigorous transformation. The main link between the totem and chart is not the knowledge itself, but my ability to perceive those links, what they mean to me: reading messages in experiences. The deeper the awareness, the more one can understand from an experience. On the contrary, a clear, face-slapping piece of wisdom will fly over the head of one whose awareness remains blind. We say the school classroom is where learning takes place, but that boxed room is minuscule compared to the 24 hours each day we live, engaging the world, connecting with those people, beings and elements we often ignore due to low awareness. Some call this Mindfulness.

Beautiful Munduk Waterfall is hidden deep in the mountains of the Munduk village in the mountain slope of west Singaraja. To get there you need to be prepared for a nice 20-30 min walk/hike. Keep your camera and valuable belonging covered as you are guaranteed to get soaked wet for the good shot ;)

I don't only collect Chess Sets. I also collect crystals and minerals. This is a anatomically correct heart shaped piece of wood that I found one day. It was open and somewhat hollow in the center, so an idea popped into my head, "I COULD PUT STONE IN THE EMPTY SPACE". I took it home and found four pieces of agate to put inside, they pieces are red, blue, green and white. I managed to fit all the stones inside the heart and got them to stay in without the use of glue. They're staying in there out of pure pressure. In my opinion, it looks like the heart of an Elemental. *** Nature's natural flu shot ***Turmeric has long been used for its many benefits because it contains potent antiviral, anti-fungal, anti-cancer, and antibacterial properties. Turmeric powder can be used to help ease symptoms of the flu, cough, and colds. It is considered a natural antibiotic because of its ability to protect the immune system from viruses and bacteria that attack it. Ingredients for homemade turmeric shots:- 1/2 lemon peeled- 1 small mandarin or clementine orange- 1 tbsp raw honey- 1 tbsp turmeric - 1 tbsp cinnamon- 1/4 tsp cloves- 1 pinch cayenne - 1 hunk of ginger #naturesflushot #turmeric #antiviral #antifungal #anticancer #antibacterial #flu #cough #cold #immunesystem #antibiotic #naturalsupport #nature #healing #health #turmeric #naturesunshineindepentdistributor

Serengeti is derived from the Maasai language, Maa; specifically, "Serengit" meaning "Endless Plains". It spans approximately 30,000 km2 (12,000 sq mi). The Kenyan part of the Serengeti is known as Maasai Mara.The Serengeti hosts the largest terrestrial mammal migration in the world, which helps secure it as one of the Seven Natural Wonders of Africa and one of the ten natural travel wonders of the world. The Serengeti is also renowned for its large lion population and is one of the best places to observe prides in their natural environment.......#picoftheday #wildlife #wild #serengueti #safari #sunset #africa #nikon #nature #naturephotography

This is humanity's medicine. This is the medicine chest. We all know Hippocrates adage, to let food be our medicine, but do we follow it? When one begins to seriously improve their diet, they will begin to notice how connected and interwoven our emotions have become to our dietetic habits. Sad? Eat some cookies. Tired? Grab a cup of coffee. Stressed, grab a burger. Depressed? Have some chocolate. You see, we use food many times as a type of sedative in order to put off having to actually face our demons and emotional issues. We just need one more hit, one more day, and then we'll deal with ourselves tomorrow! There's a whole genre of food that we simply call comfort food. What do we need to be comforted from? Why would we need a bunch of heavy, dead food if we were truly happy? Eating healthy is not easy, as we know. If it was, everyone would do it. From our earliest days, we were taught how to craftily use food to medicate ourselves. The problem is, that in the process we rob our own vitality, & in the end we end up very sick. This proves for most of us, that even if we spend our lives running from ourselves, one day nature is going to lay down the law & we will be forced to face the karma that we built. It's no easy road to be responsible for what you put into your mouth, & it's certainly not about being perfect. Nonetheless, we all have a choice. Pay the debt for incorrect eating now, or pay it later. One way or the other, the debt will be payed. Mute Swan _Ì«ÌÇå Cygnus olor _Ì«ÌÇå This large white bird is well known for its beauty and grace, but in fact seeing these in America is not a good sign because they are an invasive species. These birds are native to Europe and Asia, and they were brought to America and released into ponds as ornamental birds because of their beauty. They are very aggressive birds, they chase and attack native ducks and prevent them from nesting, and they also are very large so they can decimate native water plant populations that are not used to being consumed at such a rate. On a day when the news includes stories on the decimation of the Great Barrier Reef due to climate change/rising ocean temps and Agent Orange goes to my hometown of Detroit to talk about lifting EPA regs - I found myself at @seattleartmuseum diving into gorgeous paintings showing us places that will never look or be the same, or even exist, in the future. Losing hope isn't an option but doubling down on efforts to preserve and protect our few remaining wild and not so wild places is. What am I doing? I'm giving up red meat. I know, me. I'm donating to The Nature Conservancy as they are working to protect critical places, their inhabitants both human and animal on land and sea. And I've decided to come out of the private person closet I live in to start sharing with you all what most inspires me to keep going in the face of bad news day in and day out. There's something about the desert and the life that can be found within. The very stubbornness, tenacity, the fervour it holds for survival. From the outside looking in it seems stark, absolute, epically final in its seeming various shades of death to anyone outside life daring enough to venture in. But it's accommodating to its own. The desert is cradle to life as any forest or lake, it's just different. And the beauty of it is, she makes sure you want life bad enough. You have to want to survive, to thrive. Nothing is just handed to you, nothing taken for granted. Not a moment of sunlight, not a drop of water. What does that lesson sound like? It sounds transformative. Promising to hurt and scar along the way as you learn but the being you will shed away and grow into will be blinding for the rest of us around you. There's something about the desert, her dry voice and hot stare not luring you in at all, but waiting on you to take the plunge, allowing you to find your own lust for life and dive in. She just exists while you dance between safety and the norm and magic. She waits on you to begin. _Ì«Ì±åàyours truly _Ì«ÌÇåµ_Ì«ÌÇåµ_Ì«ÌÇ_ #desertlife #cactus #cactusgram #cacti #plantsofinstagram #transcend #awake #mantra #meditateeverydamnday #meditation #meditate #heavilymeditated #yogi #yoga #philosophy #transform #nature #naturelover #naturephotography #wild #wilderness #wildwoman #wildernessphotography #photography #plantphotography #succulents #thirdeye #inspiration #awakening #pantheism

The Round Tower at Windsor Castle in Windsor, England. The Round Tower is located on top of a 50 foot, manmade hill or motte. This position is the demarcation between the Upper and Lower Wards. This is why it is often called the Middle Ward. The constable, who heads the garrison in charge of defending the castle, lived in the upper floor apartments. Historically, this role included being governor and head of the court. Inside of this keep are several rooms including a guard chamber and dining room. The Round Tower dates back to the 12th century. An additional 30 feet were added to its height during the early 19th century.#london #england_Ì«åöÌ´_Ì«åö_ #travelpics #travelphotography #traveltheworld #ig_england #architecture #beautiful #england #instagood #travelling #sunset #nature #travel #wildlifephotography #mytravelgram #love #likesforlikes #adventures #likeforfollow #like4likeback #like4like #like4likes #like4follow #lfl #followme #likesback #like4followback #like4followers #like4likealways
